> I doubt Objective C is less verbose or more dynamic than Java<p>Oh, Objective C is certainly more dynamic. It uses a message passing mechanism. You can do this in Objective C without a compile error (note "id" is a generic object type)<p>id anObject = <i>Do some initialization</i>;
[anObject passSomeMessage];<p>The closest in Java would be:<p>Object anObject = new SomeClass();
anObject.callSomeMethod();<p>Which wouldn't compile.<p>(Please note I haven't used Objective C nor Java in a while. Please excuse any errors.)
